President Biden held a teleconference to announce several initiatives and sign an executive order addressing issues affecting Native American communities. He expressed his commitment to protecting Tribal treaty rights and increasing Tribal participation in the management of federal lands. The President also highlighted the importance of incorporating Tribal ecological knowledge to combat climate change and announced efforts to protect the Greater Chaco Landscape in New Mexico. Additionally, he addressed the crisis of violence against Native Americans and directed federal officials to work with Tribal Nations to improve public safety and advance justice. President Biden emphasized the need for Congress to pass his Build Back Better plan, which includes provisions to support Native American families and tackle the climate crisis. He signed an executive order titled "Improving Public Safety and Criminal Justice for Native Americans and Addressing the Crisis of Missing or Murdered Indigenous People."